>
  <p>
    EdgeVault is edge-native <strong>configuration</strong>, <strong>secrets</strong>, and
    <strong>feature-flag</strong> management: every value served in under 10 milliseconds from
    300+ cities, every secret envelope-encrypted, every change attributed and broadcast.
  </p>
  <p>
    It's built open-core on the Cloudflare Developer Platform. The core is MIT and self-hostable —
    no telemetry phones home, and the paid tiers say plainly what they add. We hold ourselves to
    the same standard the product enforces:
    <a href="/changelog">every change has an author and a reason</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The fastest way to know us is the code: <a href="/docs">the quickstarts</a>,
    <a href="/security">the threat model</a>, and
    <a href="https://github.com/blakebauman/edgevault">the repository</a>.
  </p>
</Prose>
